author: pburba
msg: Partial fix of issue #3067 'subtrees with intersecting mergeinfo, that don't
exist at the start of a merge range shouldn't break the merge'
* subversion/libsvn_client/merge.c
(drive_merge_report_editor): Don't make unnecessary report set_path() calls
on subtrees with intersecting mergeinfo that are themselves within another
subtree already having the same range merged.
* subversion/tests/cmdline/merge_tests.py
(new_subtrees_should_not_break_merge): Remove comment about XFail.
(test_list): Remove XFail from new_subtrees_should_not_break_merge.
